{"id":"1607.06433","submitter":"Neil Strickland","authors":"Neil Strickland","title":"Uniformization of embedded surfaces","comments":"Maple code has been uploaded as a set of ancillary files, but it can\n  be accessed more conveniently from https://neilstrickland.github.io/genus2/","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CV","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  Let X be a closed surface of genus two embedded in the 3-sphere. Then X\ninherits a metric and an orientation, which give an almost complex structure,\nwhich automatically integrates to a genuine complex structure, making X a\nRiemann surface. It follows that X is conformally isomorphic to a branched\ncover of the Riemann sphere, or to the quotient of the unit disc by the action\nof a Fuchsian group. The theorems behind these statements are important,\nwell-known, and a century old. Nonetheless, we believe that the literature\ncontains no examples where a significant fraction of the structure can be made\nexplicit. This monograph is a partially successful attempt to provide such an\nexample, starting with a particular surface X that has interesting geometry.\nThe required theory is surprisingly rich, and is supported by a large body of\nMaple code, which is used for semi-formal verification of many proofs, as well\nas for numerical calculation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Jul 2016 19:09:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-22"}
